About

I grew on up in a town by the outskirts of Boston, MA. If you were looking at a map, this town that’s south of Boston is known as Randolph, but if you were ask me, I’d call it home. Growing up with Randolph’s public school system taught me the importance of diversity – how displaced I felt once I attended a public university that made me more aware of my identity as an Asian American.

I don’t often update my linkedin… www.linkedin.com/in/michellele2002
